Welcome to Sac Luxx Rents

I’m David, a software engineer, part time teacher, and entrepreneur. Originally from Boulder Colorado but moved to California several years ago. I work for a start up in San Francisco on the weekends. I’m into Jujitsu, working out, and cooking healthy meals. Love flying, traveling, and learning new languages. I’m also a non-smoker and a US Army Veteran.
Hi, I love to travel and have found Turo to be very convenient on my own trips so I decided to share my own cars on Turo!

Hey! I’m a native Californian and huge car nerd, I enjoy sharing cars and making the whole rental experience as seamless as possible! We all know the hassle of dealing with logistics while traveling can be a burden so I’ll do my best to make it as easy as possible! Feel free to check out any of my reviews and look forward to speaking with you!
I am a USAF veteran working in the medical field, and I am local to the West Sacramento area. I am an avid car and boat enthusiast who enjoys driving and being on the water.

Say bye-bye 👋☺️ to the traditional car rentals and say Hi to my fleet of reliable & affordable rental cars 😎😎🙌🙌....we are here 24/7, 7 days a week! :). 

--
I've been doing this for quite a while now, I started in San Diego back in 2016 and now doing it here in Sacramento. 

--
couple things about me and my fleet :) 

1. Customer Service & Customer Safety are my main priorities and the rest follow behind.

2. I'm a very responsible & easy going host.. proudly a 5-star host.. my cars are very well-maintened, super reliable, great gas mileage, and super clean.

A few minor instructions and clarifications: 

1. from the minute a customer picks up the car, the customer can return the car within a 2 hour period and will process a full refund if for some reason the car does not meet the customer standards. 

2. if you are picking up / dropping off the car at my location then the entire process will be contactless.. full instructions will be sent out to you once you book the car.

3. we do offer an airport delivery option: we will meet you at the terminal outside and hand you the keys and at the drop-off time, we will meet you at the terminal outside to get the keys from you.

4. Highly recommend adding the post-cleaning option and we will take care of the cleaning for you otherwise please return the car as picked up to avoid cleaning fees. 

5. Highly recommend adding the prepaid re-fuel option and we will take care of the re-fueling otherwise please return the car as picked up to avoid gas fees. 

6. you can always extend your trip if you need to do so.. please contact me prior to your original drop-off time, you have to extend before that to avoid any delay fees. 

7. I try to keep the reservations locally so I can better serve my customers if needed.  

8. Car usually comes with at least a 1/4 tank gas. You are asked to return it with the same gas level

"The only way for me to improve is your feedbacks.."

Thank you for choosing me as your car rental host and have a great day :)

Hi! I’m originally from LA but now live in Sacramento, CA. I love how close everything is to here! Short trip away from city life in San Francisco. Tap into your inner wine snob in Napa or enjoy the breath taking views in Tahoe!

Hello, Thank you for being here to book or browse my vehicles.

My name is Avi. I’ve been in entrepreneurship since, I could work haha. It’s been a passion of mine since, I can go back. I truly have always wanted to be my own boss. 

I’ve been in customer service for over a decade and love serving others. I’ve loved this platform, it has allowed me to pursue what i’m truly passionate about. It would be a complete honor to be your host and serve you with a great electric experience in a TESLA. 

I just ask that you treat, my vehicles with the respect of your own.

Let’s do business together! Thank you again! 

My instagram is Avibainz.
